    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 13
      },
      "id": 10,
      "title": "Agent Latency \u2014 calls in the last 3 hours",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2
          },
          "unit": "s"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14
      },
      "id": 11,
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum(rate(http_client_requests_seconds_bucket{job=\"conduit-gateway\"}[5m])) by (le, client_name, uri))",
          "legendFormat": "{{client_name}} {{uri}} p95"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Agent Outbound Call Latency p95",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 0.01
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 0.05
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "percentunit"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 14
      },
      "id": 12,
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(http_client_requests_seconds_count{job=\"conduit-gateway\", outcome!=\"SUCCESS\"}[5m])) by (client_name, uri) / sum(rate(http_client_requests_seconds_count{job=\"conduit-gateway\"}[5m])) by (client_name, uri)",
          "legendFormat": "{{client_name}} error rate"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Agent Error Rate (last 5m)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 22
      },
      "id": 20,
      "title": "Intent & Auth Signals",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2
          },
          "unit": "short"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 23
      },
      "id": 21,
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(increase(chat_intent_total{job=\"conduit-gateway\"}[5m])) by (type)",
          "legendFormat": "intent: {{type}}"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Intent Classifications (5m buckets)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 23
      },
      "id": 22,
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(http_client_requests_seconds_count{job=\"conduit-gateway\", client_name=\"cerbos\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "Cerbos ABAC checks/s"
        },
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(http_client_requests_seconds_count{job=\"conduit-gateway\", client_name=\"cerbos\", outcome!=\"SUCCESS\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "Cerbos DENIED/s"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Cerbos ABAC \u2014 Check Rate & Denials",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 31
      },
      "id": 30,
      "title": "Instructions \u2014 How to use this dashboard",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 32
      },
      "id": 31,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Conversation Trace Explorer\n\n1. **Paste a Conversation ID** into the **Conversation ID** variable at the top (the gateway sets it on the root span as `span.conversation.id` and in logs as `convId`).\n2. The **Trace Search** panel shows every gateway trace for that conversation \u2014 click any row to open the full span waterfall.\n3. The **span waterfall** shows: intent classify \u2192 entity extract \u2192 Cerbos ABAC \u2192 agent fan-out (HTTP + MCP in parallel) \u2192 answer synthesis.\n4. The **Agent Latency** and **Intent/Auth** panels show aggregate signals for the selected time window.\n5. The **Conversation Logs** rows below key the same convId across every `conduit-*` service via Loki.\n\n**Key span names to look for:**\n- `chat.handle` \u2014 root gateway span (total E2E time, carries `conversation.id`)\n- `intent.classify` \u2014 LLM routing decision\n- `entity.extract` \u2014 entity extraction / identifier resolution\n- `cerbos.check` \u2014 ABAC entitlement check\n- `agent.*` \u2014 per-agent calls with `agent.id`, `agent.protocol`, `agent.model` attributes",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to use",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 38
      },
      "id": 40,
      "title": "Conversation Logs (by convId) \u2014 requires Loki",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 39
      },
      "id": 41,
      "options": {
        "content": "## How to use Conversation Logs\n\n1. **Paste a Conversation ID** into the **Conversation ID** variable at the top of this dashboard (e.g. a UUID emitted by the gateway as MDC key `convId`).\n2. The **All Logs** panel below shows every log line across all `conduit-*` services that contain that conversation ID \u2014 gateway intent classification, Cerbos ABAC decisions, agent fan-out calls and synthesis steps.\n3. The **Errors & Warnings** panel filters to `ERROR` and `WARN` lines only \u2014 use this to diagnose a failed or degraded request.\n4. **Click a `traceId` value** in any log line to jump directly to the Tempo span waterfall for that request.\n5. If no logs appear, confirm that Promtail is running (`docker compose ps promtail`) and that the gateway emits `convId` in structured JSON logs.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to use Conversation Logs",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "description": "All log lines from every Conduit service that contain the selected conversation ID \u2014 including gateway request handling, intent classification, Cerbos decisions, agent fan-out and answer synthesis. Click a traceId value to open the corresponding Tempo trace.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 12,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 43
      },
      "id": 42,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": false,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": false,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          },
          "expr": "{service=~\"gateway|conduit.*\"} |= \"$convId\"",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "All Logs for Conversation \u2014 $convId",
      "type": "logs"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "description": "ERROR and WARN log lines only for the selected conversation ID \u2014 surfaces exceptions, circuit breaker trips, Cerbos denials and synthesis failures without noise from INFO-level call tracing. Use this first when a banker reports an unexpected or incomplete answer.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 55
      },
      "id": 43,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": false,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          },
          "expr": "{service=~\"gateway|conduit.*\"} |= \"$convId\" | level =~ \"ERROR|WARN\"",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Errors and Warnings \u2014 $convId",
      "type": "logs"
    }
  ]
}